fix took ~2 minutes.\n\nThe session issues log contains entries from the PREVIOUS session (session 9) which completed story 16-8. This session (session 10) did no story work — only state repair.\n\nKey issue: This is a RECURRING problem. Ralph's state reconciliation on session start keeps overwriting committed `done` statuses back to earlier states. This has happened in sessions 6, 7, 8, 9, and now 10.\n\nRun `codeharness stats --save` to generate cost report. Read `_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/cost-report.md`.\n\nWrite the retrospective to `_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/session-retro-2026-03-27.md`. Since a retro for today already exists, append with a `---` separator and timestamp.\n\nProduce a retrospective covering:\n1. Session summary — NO_WORK session, only state corruption fix\n2. Issues analysis — the recurring state corruption problem\n3. Cost analysis — from cost report\n4. What went well — sprint 100% complete\n5. What went wrong — state corruption recurring\n6. Lessons learned\n7. Action items\n\nDo NOT ask the user any questions. Do NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.","agentId":"a06299e95d6a59225","agentType":"general-purpose","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Retrospective appended to `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/session-retro-2026-03-27.md`.\n\nSummary of what was written:\n\n- **Session 10** — NO_WORK session, ~2 minutes, only fixed state corruption in sprint-state.json (stories 16-5, 16-6, 16-7, 16-8 reverted from `done` to `review`)\n- **Critical issue** — State reconciliation (story 11-3) has corrupted `done` statuses in 5 consecutive sessions (6-10). Root cause: reconciliation does not treat `done` as a terminal state. Action item escalated to CRITICAL.\n- **Secondary issue** — Sprint counters are stale (`sprint.done` = 70, should be 74; epic-14 and epic-16 sub-counters also wrong)\n- **Cost** — $622.44 total across all sessions, $3.34 averag